Flags potential contaminant taxa from the correlation between each taxon's
relative abundance and total sample depth. Contaminants, introduced at a
roughly constant level during processing, show a \strong{negative} correlation
(their proportion is inflated in low-biomass samples). Inspired by the GRIMER
tool.

This is a pure detector: it flags taxa and returns a \link{contam_tbl} without
modifying \code{physeq}. Use \code{\link[=filter_contam_pq]{filter_contam_pq()}} to remove the flagged taxa and
\code{\link[=plot.contam_tbl]{plot.contam_tbl()}} for a quick diagnostic.
}
